edu.rit.util

Class IntSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.util.IntSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Streamable

    public class IntSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements Streamable
    Class IntSet provides a set of integers. The set can contain integers in the range 0 to N−1. In addition to the usual set operations, class IntSet provides efficient operations to add or remove randomly chosen elements and to select randomly chosen elements or non-elements.

    In the method descriptions below, "elements" refers to the integers in the range 0 to N−1 that are contained in the set. "Non-elements" refers to the integers in the range 0 to N−1 that are not contained in the set. An "empty" set is one that contains no integers. A "saturated" set is one that contains all the integers 0 to N−1.

            int off,

        Store this set's elements in a portion of the given array. This set's elements are stored starting at array index off. The order in which this set's elements appear in the array is not specified. The number of array elements stored is len. If this set contains fewer than len elements, the remaining array elements are set to 0.
